OL,3,C'We're supposed to go on holiday in 6
OL,4,Cweeks': Killer dad in police custody
OL,5,Csuite
OL,7,FHe claimed he had swiped what he
OL,8,Fthought were tongs along a work
OL,9,Fsurface, into her chest, and never
OL,10,Frealised it was a knife.
OL,12,FBut a Home Office pathologist told the
OL,13,Fcourt that the way the knife went into
OL,14,FScarlett's chest meant it must have
OL,15,Fbeen held in a hand, with force.
OL,17,FVickers had been drinking wine,
OL,18,Fwatching the Euros football tournament
OL,19,Fon television and had smoked cannabis
OL,20,Fthat day.
